    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely slice the spring onions and set aside. Peel and slice the avocado and set aside. Cut the nori into strips, if using and set aside. Finely slice the cucumber and add it to a bowl with the rice vinegar and a pinch of salt. Scrunch with your hands until slightly softened."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a bowl, mix the drained tuna with the mayonnaise, sriracha, soy sauce, sesame oil and spring onions. Taste and adjust seasoning with more soy sauce or sriracha if needed."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Divide the rice between containers. Top with a big scoop of spicy tuna, pickled cucumber, avocado and nori, if using. Sprinkle with togarashi and drizzle with more sriracha, if you like."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pop in the fridge for an easy, flavour-packed meal later. It will keep well in the fridge for 3 days."
